features.text:
#     

#
The Sphinx Gallery

Welcome to the gallery of artist CMYK. Work in this gallery will be frequently updated so come back often.

Please purchase my works by clicking on the following platform links below:
Showcasing a selection of artist's work I've collected.
LayerBreaker: Effectively, the Largest Piece of Artwork Ever Created
Lazlo Lissitsky - Unflappable, a Brief History of the Female Conservative Element 1920-1924, Scott E. Jacobus (4th Edition), 1937.
The Formation Vision Series of Works
Click Here to View on AsyncArt

The Timepiece of Thades is a autonomous programmed piece of artwork on AsyncArt using 24 images that update on the hour, every hour, forever...

The work is geometric abstract minimalism and uses my particular CMYK hexadecimal set.

The piece is optimized for widescreen TVs/Monitors & Apple TV with a 16:9 aspect ratio for full-screen viewing.

Read more details about The Timepiece of Thades by clicking to my Medium article below...

The Formation Vision series are 9 pieces of work that focus on psychology of self, physics and metaphysics.

Each piece was created with an overriding concept that would be played out forever in the form of a perception altering artwork.

The series was released across two platforms, both Opensea (5/5s) and KnownOrigin (3/3s & one 1/1).

The works are now only available on the secondary market...

The House of Frarny series of works all focus on the main character, Frarny, a shapeshifting cypher of a character that gets involved in all kinds of strangeness.

The only thing that never changes about Frarny is his head (except in the piece to your left).

Frarny has been referred to by many as a bear, a monkey, a robot and many more things besides. The only thing certain about what he actually is, is that I'm not telling :)

He is whatever you want or believe him to be...

Lolz Biscuit - 3/3 / Dogecoin NFT

Lolz Biscuit is the first Gif/moving image ever minted to Dogecoin as an NFT. It was minted at block 3,922,298 under the Dogeparty protocol asset name, 'CMYK.LOLZBISCUIT' as an edition of 3.

Dogemaster 1, 'MOON' - 100/100 

Dogecoin NFT Collectible Card

Dogemaster 'Moon' is the first ever NFT collectible card minted to the Dogecoin chain. It was fully minted (name asset & image) at block 3,923,891 under the Dogeparty protocol asset name, 'DOGEMASTERCD' by CMYK as an edition of 100.

The following cards in the series all use the Dogemaster prefix with a sub-asset name, eg. 'DOGEMASTERCD.NOTIMETODEFI' (pictured right)

The Dogemaster cards are all examples of crypto-art proper.

'Overlord' - 5/5 / Dogecoin NFT

Series: Super Supremacy Supreme

'Overlord' is the first digital artwork ever minted to Dogecoin as an NFT. It was minted at block 3,917,541 under the Dogeparty protocol asset name, 'CMYK.OVERLORD' as an edition of 10 that then had 5 burned, leaving a remaining 5.

The Super Supremacy Supreme series deals with issues of power, abuse of power & technology used as a means of control - now & in the future.
